you know,
"sell by" date stuff.

1092
01:06:43,667 --> 01:06:45,033
Oh.

1093
01:06:46,702 --> 01:06:48,203
So did you get to
meet Castro?

1094
01:06:49,405 --> 01:06:50,605
Who?

1095
01:06:50,607 --> 01:06:52,273
Did you get to meet Castro?

1096
01:06:52,275 --> 01:06:53,608
Yes, I did, actually.
About two weeks

1097
01:06:53,610 --> 01:06:55,110
after Kennedy
was assassinated.

1098
01:06:55,112 --> 01:06:57,379
Talking of which, Frank,

1099
01:06:57,381 --> 01:07:00,081
I'm starting to remember
more and more who I am

1100
01:07:00,083 --> 01:07:01,783
and who I was
and the weapons I made.

1101
01:07:01,785 --> 01:07:04,352
My God,
it really is amazing.

1102
01:07:04,354 --> 01:07:07,589
How efficiently
those boys from MI6,
may God bless 'em...

1103
01:07:07,591 --> 01:07:09,257
But you know something, Frank?

1104
01:07:09,259 --> 01:07:10,759
They really do throw us away.
Don't they, old sport?

1105
01:07:10,761 --> 01:07:13,461
When we're no longer
convenient, I suppose.

1106
01:07:13,463 --> 01:07:14,662
As though
we'd never given them

1107
01:07:14,664 --> 01:07:16,097
the best years of our lives.

1108
01:07:16,099 --> 01:07:17,298
Bit of a joke, really.

1109
01:07:18,501 --> 01:07:20,168
Yes, very strange.

1110
01:07:22,238 --> 01:07:24,039
Do you remember
where Nightshade is?

1111
01:07:25,508 --> 01:07:27,142
I'm sorry, my dear?

1112
01:07:27,144 --> 01:07:28,676
Do you remember
where Nightshade is?

1113
01:07:29,678 --> 01:07:31,079
Oh, yes.

1114
01:07:32,748 --> 01:07:34,149
Now, this feels right.

1115
01:07:37,553 --> 01:07:41,222
It's around here somewhere.
I'm sure this time.

1116
01:07:41,224 --> 01:07:43,691
Everything looks
different completely.

1117
01:07:43,693 --> 01:07:45,226
Maybe it's over here.

1118
01:07:45,228 --> 01:07:46,428
It's been hours. Hours.

1119
01:07:46,430 --> 01:07:48,196
BAILEY: Yeah, this is it.

1120
01:07:48,198 --> 01:07:50,231
Here we are.

1121
01:07:50,233 --> 01:07:52,067
How are those Jimmy Choos
working out for you?

1122
01:07:53,335 --> 01:07:54,469
The entrance is up there.

1123
01:07:56,205 --> 01:07:57,572
Who's Papa John?

1124
01:07:57,574 --> 01:07:58,673
MARVIN: It's new.

1125
01:07:58,675 --> 01:08:00,809
Entrance to what?

1126
01:08:00,811 --> 01:08:03,411
BAILEY: Secret tunnels
through the old catacombs.

1127
01:08:03,413 --> 01:08:05,180
Brezhnev used it
to sneak his mistress in.

1128
01:08:05,182 --> 01:08:06,214
SARAH: In where?
BAILEY: In there.

1129
01:08:08,584 --> 01:08:10,685
FRANK: The Kremlin?

1130
01:08:10,687 --> 01:08:12,587
The weapon is
in the Kremlin?

1131
01:08:12,589 --> 01:08:14,089
It's the one place
they wouldn't look.

1132
01:08:21,430 --> 01:08:23,131
(HAMMERING)

1133
01:08:32,341 --> 01:08:34,309
Jesus. Do you mind
keeping it warm?

1134
01:08:50,326 --> 01:08:53,461
PHILIPS: You have no idea
the damage you've done.

1135
01:08:53,463 --> 01:08:56,698
You kept one of our own
locked up for 32 years.

1136
01:08:56,700 --> 01:08:58,566
I have kept the world safe.

1137
01:08:58,568 --> 01:08:59,734
If that weapon
falls into the wrong hands...

1138
01:08:59,736 --> 01:09:01,636
The weapon?

1139
01:09:01,638 --> 01:09:05,874
(SIGHING) You haven't
the slightest idea.

1140
01:09:12,348 --> 01:09:13,748
You must let me call Moses.

1141
01:09:13,750 --> 01:09:16,284
He doesn't know
what he's walking into.

1142
01:09:16,286 --> 01:09:19,187
You've had your chance.
It's over.

1143
01:09:20,623 --> 01:09:22,490
I'm sorry, Victoria.

1144
01:09:27,463 --> 01:09:29,264
(SCOFFS)

1145
01:09:29,266 --> 01:09:31,232
Sorry, my ass.
(DOOR CLOSING)

1146
01:09:33,169 --> 01:09:34,269
They say
you're a legend around here.

1147
01:09:35,271 --> 01:09:36,171
I've...

1148
01:09:37,640 --> 01:09:40,241
I've never heard of you.

1149
01:09:40,243 --> 01:09:42,343
Must have been
a bit before my time.

1150
01:09:43,546 --> 01:09:44,546
(GRUNTS)

1151
01:09:46,448 --> 01:09:47,782
(GROANS)

1152
01:09:47,784 --> 01:09:49,184
(HANDCUFFS CLICK)

1153
01:09:49,186 --> 01:09:50,752
Well, you've heard
of me now.

1154
01:09:54,190 --> 01:09:55,924
How is it possible
they never picked up

1155
01:09:55,926 --> 01:09:58,293
the radiation signature
from that bomb?

1156
01:09:58,295 --> 01:10:00,528
That's the
million dollar question.

1157
01:10:02,198 --> 01:10:05,333
Hey, gang. This is new.

1158
01:10:05,335 --> 01:10:07,202
What do you think
is behind that wall?

1159
01:10:08,304 --> 01:10:09,804
Um...

1160
01:10:09,806 --> 01:10:10,972
I think Russians.

1161
01:10:35,698 --> 01:10:38,666
If anybody sees that hole,
we're dead.

1162
01:10:38,668 --> 01:10:40,468
I'm gonna need you to help me
to disarm the weapon.

1163
01:10:40,470 --> 01:10:42,570
Frank, somebody's
gotta guard the door.

1164
01:10:42,572 --> 01:10:43,538
(STAMMERS)

1165
01:10:43,540 --> 01:10:45,240
No.
But...

1166
01:10:47,476 --> 01:10:48,543
MARVIN: You'll need this.

1167
01:10:55,718 --> 01:10:59,354
(SPEAKING RUSSIAN)

1168
01:10:59,356 --> 01:11:02,290
(REPLIES IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE)

1169
01:11:02,292 --> 01:11:03,291
FRANK: One more time.

1170
01:11:04,627 --> 01:11:08,963
(SARAH SPEAKING RUSSIAN)

1171
01:11:08,965 --> 01:11:10,632
Great. Great.
What does that mean?

1172
01:11:10,634 --> 01:11:13,268
"Gas leak.
Maintenance is coming."

1173
01:11:13,270 --> 01:11:14,269
Good.
And then they'll move on.

1174
01:11:14,271 --> 01:11:15,470
SARAH:
And what if they don't?

1175
01:11:15,472 --> 01:11:17,438
Want a gun?
Yes.

1176
01:11:17,440 --> 01:11:18,740
No. No gun.

1177
01:11:18,742 --> 01:11:20,475
Just don't move.

1178
01:11:20,477 --> 01:11:22,810
You're a security guard.

1179
01:11:22,812 --> 01:11:24,779
Don't smile.
You can't smile.

1180
01:11:24,781 --> 01:11:27,949
(SPEAKING RUSSIAN)

1181
01:11:27,951 --> 01:11:30,351
You just never leave
your post. Okay?

1182
01:11:31,620 --> 01:11:32,754
Nice.

1183
01:11:46,669 --> 01:11:48,436
Two shots, here and here.

1184
01:11:48,438 --> 01:11:50,772
Drag the body in there
and repeat as necessary.

1185
01:11:50,774 --> 01:11:52,006
No safety.

1186
01:11:52,008 --> 01:11:52,974
No safety.

1187
01:12:08,457 --> 01:12:12,327
MARVIN: Frank, I don't like
the Kremlin so much.

1188
01:12:12,329 --> 01:12:16,531
And I like being
underneath it even less.

1189
01:12:33,415 --> 01:12:36,084
That's great.
It's just like yesterday.

1190
01:12:38,420 --> 01:12:40,521
There's my wrench or crow bar.
Look at this.

1191
01:12:41,657 --> 01:12:43,791
There.

1192
01:12:43,793 --> 01:12:45,626
Hey, look, chaps.

1193
01:12:45,628 --> 01:12:47,795
That's my old pipe.
I knew I'd left it somewhere.

1194
01:12:47,797 --> 01:12:49,964
My dear wife bought this
the fifth, 1969.

1195
01:12:49,966 --> 01:12:51,666
It was our
wedding anniversary.

1196
01:12:51,668 --> 01:12:52,567
Oh, yes! This is, um...

1197
01:12:53,969 --> 01:12:56,604
This is Nightshade,
by the way.

1198
01:13:02,444 --> 01:13:03,578
There.

1199
01:13:05,013 --> 01:13:06,414
Is that...

1200
01:13:06,416 --> 01:13:07,081
That's Red Mercury.

1201
01:13:08,484 --> 01:13:10,151
Red Mercury?

1202
01:13:10,153 --> 01:13:12,754
We were always told
it was a Cold War myth.

1203
01:13:12,756 --> 01:13:15,022
Yes, they said
it couldn't be done,
but I did it. See?

1204
01:13:15,024 --> 01:13:16,758
Frank,
if that's Red Mercury,

1205
01:13:16,760 --> 01:13:18,426
you can zip it up
in a backpack

1206
01:13:18,428 --> 01:13:19,694
and take it
on the White House tour.

1207
01:13:19,696 --> 01:13:21,462
It's undetectable.

1208
01:13:21,464 --> 01:13:24,665
No signature.
No fallout.

1209
01:13:24,667 --> 01:13:26,801
BAILEY: This is a weapon
that will entirely change

1210
01:13:26,803 --> 01:13:28,569
the balance
of international power

1211
01:13:28,571 --> 01:13:31,105
overnight. Just like that.

1212
01:13:31,107 --> 01:13:31,973
MARVIN:
We're all gonna die.

1213
01:13:33,175 --> 01:13:34,108
On your knees.

1214
01:13:37,679 --> 01:13:39,947
Katja.

1215
01:13:39,949 --> 01:13:42,617
No government
should have this weapon.

1216
01:13:42,619 --> 01:13:44,719
Not yours. And not mine.

1217
01:13:45,721 --> 01:13:48,589
I have orders.

1218
01:13:48,591 --> 01:13:51,058
This isn't about orders.
This is about right and wrong.

1219
01:13:52,060 --> 01:13:53,060
Don't.

1220
01:13:55,464 --> 01:13:57,064
Did you really come
to see me in the States?

1221
01:13:58,066 --> 01:13:59,100
Yes.

1222
01:14:00,669 --> 01:14:03,037
What color were the flowers
outside my house?

1223
01:14:10,813 --> 01:14:12,013
Yellow.

1224
01:14:24,126 --> 01:14:26,894
(SPEAKING RUSSIAN)

1225
01:14:33,502 --> 01:14:34,702
(CHUCKLES)

1226
01:15:09,838 --> 01:15:12,974
What in the name of... Hey!

1227
01:15:12,976 --> 01:15:15,009
(GUARD GRUNTS)

1228
01:15:15,011 --> 01:15:16,878
What are you doing
kissing this guy?

1229
01:15:16,880 --> 01:15:18,045
I didn't wanna kill him.

1230
01:15:18,047 --> 01:15:20,748
What kinda
stupid logic is that?

1231
01:15:20,750 --> 01:15:22,617
What in the Sam Hill
is she doing here?

1232
01:15:22,619 --> 01:15:24,519
She's working with us again.

1233
01:15:24,521 --> 01:15:25,786
Like heck she is.

1234
01:15:25,788 --> 01:15:27,655
Why were you
kissing that guy?

1235
01:15:27,657 --> 01:15:31,192
Kids, what happens
in the Kremlin
stays in the Kremlin.

1236
01:15:31,194 --> 01:15:33,528
(ALARM BLARING IN DISTANCE)

1237
01:15:33,530 --> 01:15:36,030
You are gonna have to
explain this to me.

1238
01:15:59,087 --> 01:16:00,888
Hey, Comrades!

1239
01:16:00,890 --> 01:16:02,290
Here's to more success.

1240
01:16:02,292 --> 01:16:03,758
Success.

1241
01:16:03,760 --> 01:16:04,926
SARAH: And saving the world!

1242
01:16:04,928 --> 01:16:06,761
Saving the world!

1243
01:16:06,763 --> 01:16:07,962
KATJA: <i>Na zdorovie!</i>

1244
01:16:07,964 --> 01:16:09,030
<i>Na zdorovie!</i>

1245
01:16:09,032 --> 01:16:10,298
(STUTTERING)

1246
01:16:12,935 --> 01:16:14,735
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

1247
01:16:15,737 --> 01:16:18,639
I got this. Right back.

1248
01:16:18,641 --> 01:16:20,107
Hey.

1249
01:16:20,109 --> 01:16:21,208
Where are you?

1250
01:16:21,210 --> 01:16:22,910
Moscow.

1251
01:16:22,912 --> 01:16:24,812
He's a nutter, Francis.

1252
01:16:24,814 --> 01:16:27,281
MI6 didn't lock him up
because he created the weapon

1253
01:16:27,283 --> 01:16:28,950
but because
he wants to see it go off.

1254
01:16:30,919 --> 01:16:32,186
(GUN CLICKS)

1255
01:16:34,356 --> 01:16:35,790
Hello, Frank.

1256
01:16:36,992 --> 01:16:39,293
That was Victoria, wasn't it?

1257
01:16:39,295 --> 01:16:42,196
Telling you that I was
some sort of a monster

1258
01:16:42,198 --> 01:16:46,067
who once wanted to destroy
the Soviet empire.

1259
01:16:46,069 --> 01:16:49,103
Yeah. Very slowly.

1260
01:16:51,373 --> 01:16:53,107
That's it. Good boy.

1261
01:16:58,947 --> 01:17:01,082
Good. In you go.

1262
01:17:02,384 --> 01:17:03,184
Marvin...

1263
01:17:04,386 --> 01:17:05,786
Guns down.

1264
01:17:14,129 --> 01:17:16,230
BAILEY: Weapons down.
Very slowly.

1265
01:17:18,867 --> 01:17:21,636
You planted the thing
on WikiLeaks.

1266
01:17:21,638 --> 01:17:25,106
Oh, yes, it was a cell phone
taken from a guard.

1267
01:17:25,108 --> 01:17:28,376
I was just itching to get
my revenge on MI6, you see.

1268
01:17:28,378 --> 01:17:29,844
Frank, you were
absolutely marvelous

1269
01:17:29,846 --> 01:17:31,712
the way you found The Frog.

1270
01:17:31,714 --> 01:17:33,180
No one else
could have found him.

1271
01:17:33,182 --> 01:17:34,148
Jack?

1272
01:17:36,151 --> 01:17:37,852
Sorry, Frank,
I made a deal already

1273
01:17:37,854 --> 01:17:39,987
with Mr. Horton
for Red Mercury.

1274
01:17:39,989 --> 01:17:42,757
Well done, Bailey.
Thanks.

1275
01:17:42,759 --> 01:17:43,691
HORTON:
Nice to see you again, Frank.

1276
01:17:43,693 --> 01:17:46,093
Pick up the guns.

1277
01:17:46,095 --> 01:17:48,396
Your country appreciates
your sacrifice, Frank.

1278
01:17:50,298 --> 01:17:51,766
But your time's up.

1279
01:17:53,168 --> 01:17:54,068
Let's go.

1280
01:17:56,071 --> 01:17:57,738
It's time, Bailey.

1281
01:17:57,740 --> 01:17:58,706
Yes, it is time.

1282
01:18:01,410 --> 01:18:03,010
Very Interesting.

1283
01:18:03,012 --> 01:18:06,847
Rogue American agents
turned nuclear terrorists

1284
01:18:06,849 --> 01:18:08,082
kill top Russian officer.

1285
01:18:09,084 --> 01:18:11,152
Not good.

1286
01:18:11,154 --> 01:18:12,820
So long, Frank.
So long, Marvin.

1287
01:18:14,423 --> 01:18:15,823
Come on, boys, let's go.

1288
01:18:21,463 --> 01:18:23,698
Easy. Easy.

1289
01:18:41,483 --> 01:18:43,150
(INDISTINCT SHOUTING)

1290
01:18:57,332 --> 01:19:00,234
Oh, please,
let me take that from you.

1291
01:19:00,236 --> 01:19:02,837
I thought we were doing
the debriefing in London.

1292
01:19:02,839 --> 01:19:04,205
HORTON: Oh, we were.

1293
01:19:04,207 --> 01:19:06,006
But since you're such a sick,
twisted bastard,

1294
01:19:06,008 --> 01:19:07,174
you're going to Colorado.

1295
01:19:07,176 --> 01:19:08,509
There's a secret
facility there,

1296
