01:35:52,214 --> 01:35:53,179
Are you okay?

1555
01:35:55,382 --> 01:35:56,883
Hah!

1556
01:35:56,885 --> 01:35:57,951
Awesome!

1557
01:36:16,203 --> 01:36:17,270
Oh, shit.

1558
01:36:17,272 --> 01:36:18,438
Is that it?

1559
01:36:18,440 --> 01:36:20,039
It's counting down, Frank.

1560
01:36:20,041 --> 01:36:21,775
Shut it off. Right?

1561
01:36:21,777 --> 01:36:24,844
(STUTTERS) Shut... Yeah.
With what? Acupressure?

1562
01:36:24,846 --> 01:36:26,279
I don't know.

1563
01:36:26,281 --> 01:36:28,148
Well, why is it
my responsibility?

1564
01:36:29,216 --> 01:36:30,817
HAN: Just do something.

1565
01:36:30,819 --> 01:36:33,119
MARVIN: With my
Mr. Chemistry set?

1566
01:36:34,288 --> 01:36:36,156
I don't know
what I'm doing.

1567
01:36:36,158 --> 01:36:38,358
You want me
to push a button?

1568
01:36:38,360 --> 01:36:39,559
Bailey's loose
and the bomb's ticking.

1569
01:36:44,565 --> 01:36:46,299
GUARD: Wait. Excuse me, ma'am.

1570
01:36:46,301 --> 01:36:47,834
Hello, I have an appointment.

1571
01:36:51,105 --> 01:36:53,039
WOMAN: Gun!
(ALL SCREAMING)

1572
01:37:18,199 --> 01:37:19,299
Get that bomb outta here.

1573
01:37:25,339 --> 01:37:26,472
Drop it now, darling.
That's right.

1574
01:37:26,474 --> 01:37:27,340
SARAH: My gun!

1575
01:37:34,481 --> 01:37:35,515
Press the button.
Ground floor.

1576
01:37:36,917 --> 01:37:38,384
Marvin, let's go!

1577
01:37:42,356 --> 01:37:44,023
(GRUNTING)

1578
01:37:44,025 --> 01:37:45,525
Jolly good show.

1579
01:37:45,527 --> 01:37:46,993
(CAR ENGINE STARTS)

1580
01:37:52,199 --> 01:37:53,132
Bollocks.

1581
01:37:58,906 --> 01:38:01,507
You really drive
this ridiculous thing?

1582
01:38:01,509 --> 01:38:02,876
Can you shoot?

1583
01:38:02,878 --> 01:38:04,077
(ENGINE REVVING)

1584
01:38:09,116 --> 01:38:10,583
We need eyes, Francis.

1585
01:38:24,231 --> 01:38:26,165
Come on, Frank.
Forty minutes.

1586
01:38:35,409 --> 01:38:37,043
Marvin, how ya
doin' back there?

1587
01:38:37,045 --> 01:38:38,544
(MUFFLED) I can't talk
to you right now.

1588
01:38:40,481 --> 01:38:41,681
(GASPS)

1589
01:38:41,683 --> 01:38:43,283
How is it?

1590
01:38:43,285 --> 01:38:44,217
It's fine.

1591
01:38:47,922 --> 01:38:49,022
Shit!

1592
01:38:53,260 --> 01:38:55,094
Show me something.

1593
01:38:55,096 --> 01:38:56,496
(TIRES SCREECHING)

1594
01:39:20,654 --> 01:39:22,288
FRANK: <i>Victoria,</i>

1595
01:39:22,290 --> 01:39:24,457
I got eyes on.
Bailey's heading for the M4.

1596
01:39:24,459 --> 01:39:25,558
Got it.

1597
01:39:27,594 --> 01:39:28,494
MARVIN: Got it!

1598
01:39:30,197 --> 01:39:32,065
This one should stop it

1599
01:39:32,067 --> 01:39:33,967
and this one
should detonate it.

1600
01:39:33,969 --> 01:39:35,134
It's fifty-fifty, Frank.

1601
01:39:38,105 --> 01:39:39,238
Wait!

1602
01:39:39,240 --> 01:39:40,139
(BEEPING RAPIDLY)

1603
01:39:41,141 --> 01:39:43,376
That's weird.

1604
01:39:43,378 --> 01:39:44,410
Do you have any idea
what you're doing?

1605
01:39:47,047 --> 01:39:48,281
Wait, wait!

1606
01:39:48,283 --> 01:39:49,482
Wait!

1607
01:39:49,484 --> 01:39:50,750
(BEEPING FASTER)
Stop cutting wires!

1608
01:39:50,752 --> 01:39:52,552
I knew we were gonna die!

1609
01:39:55,222 --> 01:39:56,456
Ready to kill
this son of a bitch?

1610
01:39:56,458 --> 01:39:58,224
Abso-bloody-lutely.

1611
01:40:00,594 --> 01:40:01,694
Damn it!

1612
01:40:06,667 --> 01:40:08,134
Trouble.

1613
01:40:08,136 --> 01:40:09,369
<i>Marvin!</i>

1614
01:40:09,371 --> 01:40:12,472
Frank, it's two pedals
and two sticks.

1615
01:40:12,474 --> 01:40:13,406
Okay.

1616
01:40:20,047 --> 01:40:21,247
(TRUCK HONKING)

1617
01:40:50,677 --> 01:40:53,179
Damn it! We missed him.
He's going into the airport.

1618
01:40:53,181 --> 01:40:54,447
FRANK: <i>Go get him!</i>

1619
01:40:54,449 --> 01:40:56,749
Well, where are you?
In trouble.

1620
01:40:56,751 --> 01:40:59,385
POLICE: <i>Turn back!</i>
<i>You are in</i>
<i>restricted airspace.</i>

1621
01:40:59,387 --> 01:41:01,054
Frank, they're gonna blow us
outta the sky.

1622
01:41:01,056 --> 01:41:02,355
I wouldn't worry about that.

1623
01:41:02,357 --> 01:41:03,189
The engine's shutting down.

1624
01:41:04,191 --> 01:41:05,758
Mayday! Mayday!

1625
01:41:05,760 --> 01:41:07,093
MARVIN: Frank!

1626
01:41:08,295 --> 01:41:10,229
I knew we were gonna die!

1627
01:41:10,231 --> 01:41:11,330
POLICE:
<i>This is your last warning!</i>

1628
01:41:11,332 --> 01:41:12,532
Oh, please,
tell me you're not crashing

1629
01:41:12,534 --> 01:41:14,167
with a weapon
of mass destruction.

1630
01:41:17,337 --> 01:41:19,072
MARVIN: No, Frank, no.

1631
01:41:24,845 --> 01:41:26,145
Oh, God.

1632
01:41:28,682 --> 01:41:30,116
(TIMER BEEPING)

1633
01:41:35,756 --> 01:41:37,256
(GRUNTING)

1634
01:41:39,126 --> 01:41:40,560
You okay back there, Marvin?

1635
01:41:40,562 --> 01:41:43,863
It wasn't exactly
a three-point landing, Frank.

1636
01:41:43,865 --> 01:41:45,131
How's the bomb doing?

1637
01:41:48,469 --> 01:41:49,836
I can't stop it.

1638
01:42:03,750 --> 01:42:05,251
FRANK: We gotta
get it outta here.

1639
01:42:06,820 --> 01:42:08,621
Hey! Hey!

1640
01:42:08,623 --> 01:42:09,722
Get outta the car.

1641
01:42:21,735 --> 01:42:23,536
BAILEY: Hello, Frank.

1642
01:42:23,538 --> 01:42:24,537
Welcome aboard.

1643
01:42:27,708 --> 01:42:29,642
Always the good soldier,
aren't you?

1644
01:42:31,512 --> 01:42:33,279
Stalemate.

1645
01:42:33,281 --> 01:42:35,581
How will you take him out

1646
01:42:35,583 --> 01:42:37,150
and not shoot her first?

1647
01:42:38,886 --> 01:42:41,921
Frank, it's okay.

1648
01:42:41,923 --> 01:42:43,890
You can shoot.
It's okay.

1649
01:42:45,292 --> 01:42:48,161
BAILEY: Put the gun down.

1650
01:42:49,196 --> 01:42:50,163
Put the gun down!

1651
01:42:52,466 --> 01:42:53,799
Drop the gun!

1652
01:42:56,770 --> 01:43:00,239
Put the gun down, Frankie.

1653
01:43:01,475 --> 01:43:02,708
Thank you.

1654
01:43:04,178 --> 01:43:05,378
Pretty smart.

1655
01:43:06,880 --> 01:43:09,582
So love does conquer all.

1656
01:43:10,784 --> 01:43:12,451
Go to your golden warrior.

1657
01:43:15,355 --> 01:43:16,255
That's a good girl.

1658
01:43:18,492 --> 01:43:19,592
Aw!

1659
01:43:22,496 --> 01:43:23,763
FRANK: Come here.

1660
01:43:23,765 --> 01:43:26,365
BAILEY: Ah! It's so sweet.

1661
01:43:28,268 --> 01:43:31,804
Now leave the plane.
Take Nightshade with you.

1662
01:43:33,807 --> 01:43:34,941
Bye, Frank.

1663
01:43:37,444 --> 01:43:38,711
Sweet dreams.

1664
01:43:54,928 --> 01:43:56,629
Why didn't you
just shoot me?

1665
01:44:15,515 --> 01:44:16,782
What happened?

1666
01:44:16,784 --> 01:44:17,950
I couldn't disarm it.

1667
01:44:26,260 --> 01:44:27,760
Oh, crap.

1668
01:44:27,762 --> 01:44:29,595
(MUTTERS IN KOREAN)

1669
01:44:29,597 --> 01:44:30,997
Marvin,

1670
01:44:30,999 --> 01:44:32,832
it's going to detonate?

1671
01:44:32,834 --> 01:44:34,333
Yeah.

1672
01:44:34,335 --> 01:44:35,368
Put your arms around me.

1673
01:44:38,772 --> 01:44:39,905
(SIGHS)

1674
01:44:45,312 --> 01:44:46,946
(WHISTLING SOFTLY)

1675
01:44:46,948 --> 01:44:48,781
(RAPID BEEPING)

1676
01:44:58,592 --> 01:44:59,759
Oh...

1677
01:45:01,595 --> 01:45:02,962
I didn't see that one coming.

1678
01:45:04,998 --> 01:45:06,399
(DISTANT EXPLOSION)

1679
01:45:22,516 --> 01:45:24,617
There's something
you don't see every day.

1680
01:45:30,357 --> 01:45:31,757
VICTORIA: You put the bomb
on the plane.

1681
01:45:35,595 --> 01:45:38,898
And, um, you didn't think
to mention that?

1682
01:45:38,900 --> 01:45:40,833
You blew up my plane.

1683
01:45:40,835 --> 01:45:42,435
Sorry.

1684
01:45:42,437 --> 01:45:44,637
I was wrong?
So we're not even gonna die?

1685
01:45:45,639 --> 01:45:46,739
Not yet.

1686
01:45:48,408 --> 01:45:50,609
I was actually
starting to like you.

1687
01:45:50,611 --> 01:45:52,678
I was even thinking about
not killing you.

1688
01:45:52,680 --> 01:45:54,914
This is what happens when
you try to save the world.

1689
01:45:54,916 --> 01:45:56,682
Han. Han, you can't

1690
01:45:56,684 --> 01:45:58,084
put a price
on these things.
Uh-uh.

1691
01:45:58,086 --> 01:46:00,386
You owe me 30 mil
for the plane.

1692
01:46:00,388 --> 01:46:02,788
And 20 for not killing you.

1693
01:46:02,790 --> 01:46:04,657
You're a dead man, Moses.

1694
01:46:06,760 --> 01:46:08,094
Thanks for your help.

1695
01:46:09,796 --> 01:46:10,996
Really.

1696
01:46:13,500 --> 01:46:14,700
You think he means it?

1697
01:46:14,702 --> 01:46:16,435
Nah, he's a nice guy.

1698
01:46:16,437 --> 01:46:17,737
I mean it, Frank!

1699
01:46:17,739 --> 01:46:19,004
All right.

1700
01:46:22,609 --> 01:46:24,076
VICTORIA: Aw!

1701
01:46:24,078 --> 01:46:25,778
They're going to be
right as rain.

1702
01:46:28,081 --> 01:46:31,117
He made the run
to emotional safety.

1703
01:46:35,655 --> 01:46:37,990
FRANK: So...

1704
01:46:37,992 --> 01:46:39,825
I did hear
about this job in Caracas.

1705
01:46:41,795 --> 01:46:43,028
And?

1706
01:46:44,698 --> 01:46:46,499
(UPBEAT MUSIC PLAYING)

1707
01:46:49,136 --> 01:46:50,870
(PATRONS SCREAMING)

1708
01:46:55,509 --> 01:46:57,143
(SARAH CONTINUES FIRING)

1709
01:46:57,145 --> 01:46:59,678
Don't look at me.
She's your girlfriend.

1710
01:47:03,583 --> 01:47:04,517
Oh.

1711
01:47:05,519 --> 01:47:06,819
Come on.

1712
01:47:06,821 --> 01:47:08,788
(UPBEAT MUSIC PLAYING)
